The outputs generated will be with the following function/inputs
C = drugDiffusion1D(0.1, 1, 5, 50, 20000, 0.05);
While following this format
[C] = drugDiffusion1D(D, L, T, Nx, Nt, decay)
D: Diffusion Constant
L: Length of whatever the drug is flowing through. 
T: Total time the drug is diffusing. The time that the simulation is going through.
Nx: The number of points that we are dividing the length into.
Nt: The number of points that we are dividing the time into.
decay: The decay Constant, how fast the drug is breaking down/dissolving in the simulation.
